Class 4


Service:

By default we can't access pods in kuberenetes.
If we want to access then we need to expose pods, to do this we use services

Kuberenetes Services:
Cluster-IP: This type of service is used expose the pods within the cluster. It provides a stable IP.
            By usimng this stable IP we can access the application internally (within the server)
NodePort: this type of service is used to expose the pods. It provides a stable Ip and nodePort.
          It has a range from 30000 to 32767 
LoadBalancer: this type of service is used to expose the pods. It provides a stable Ip and nodePort and DNS(Domain Name System)
             Instead of using IP address for accessing the application we can use DNS (ex: http:192.168.2.1.80 (http:www.facebbok.com))


