Class 7 

Staefulset and DeamonSet

Statesless Application:
1. It can't store the data permanently.
2. The word STATELESS means no past data.
3. It depends on non-persistent data means data is removed when Pod, Node or Cluster is stopped.
4. Non persistent mainly used for logging info (ex: systtem log, container log etc.,)
5. In order to avoid this problem, we are using stateful appliaction.
6. A stateless application can be deployed as a set of identical replicas and each replica can handle incoming requests independently without the need to coordinate with other replicas.

Staeful Application:
  Stateful appliactions are appliactions that store data and keep tracking it.
  
  ex of stateful appliactions
  . All RDS databases(MYSQL, SQL)
  . Elastic search, kafka, MangoDB Redis etc.,
  . Any appliactionthat stores data
In stateful applications 
Primary pod--> read and write permission
Secondar Pod--> read permission only

